Sequence Information.Family: Belongs to the frog skin active peptide (FSAP) family. Brevinin subfamily
Sequence Information.Target Organism: [Ref.22828809]Gram-negative bacterium:B.dysenteriae (MIC=35 μg/ml);Gram-positive bacteria:S.aureus ATCC 2592 (MIC=4.7 μg/ml), B.subtilis ATCC 6633 (MIC=9.38 μg/ml);Fungus:C.albicans (MIC=18.75 μg/ml)
Sequence Information.Hemolytic Activity: [Ref.22828809] It exhibits hemolysis of 1.32%, 5.37%, 6.35%, 16.55% at 25 μg/ml, 50 μg/ml, 100 μg/ml, 200 μg/ml against rabbit red blood cells
Sequence Information.Cytotoxicity: No cytotoxicity information found in the reference(s) presented
Sequence Information.Function: Has activity against Gram- negative bacterium and exhibits hemolytic activity.

Literature.Title: Antimicrobial peptide diversity in the skin of the torrent frog,Amolops jingdongensis.
